race.comment: SHOT DOWN BY LOVE (6) caused an upset when winning her penultimate start here over this trip, and then was fourth last time out over a mile nearly 3 weeks ago. She has a better gate now, and she will be hard to hold out again. PEACH GALANTES (9) has been racing consistently and fought on well enough for third here last time out. She is drawn closer to the fence this time and should produce her usual honest effort. Each way all day. ROYAL CHARGE (4) is better than his form suggests, and this is his pet trip. He has recently changed stables and might be one to boost any top 4 combos. TOBA (2) ran the race of an improver at Warwick 2 weeks ago, and he does have a good record on this course. He gets a more favourable draw third up and is ready to put his best hoof forward. JEDIAH (5) was an overdue maiden winner at Toowoomba earlier last month, and was close to that form again when finishing fourth at Kilcoy last week. Stick with him on an each-way basis.
